Primary_Text:
There is no politeness distinction in Lezgian personal pronouns,
although the 2nd pl is sometimes used as a polite form of address,
certainly under the influence of Russian as the main lingua franca
in that area.

If a pronoun is used to address or refer to one or more persons
in the following categories the pronouns must be the plural form:
(i) a female relative through marriage of a male ego (except wife
of ego); (ii) the wife of a male cross-cousin of a male ego; (iii)
husband's brother; and (iv) the husband of a female cross-cousin of
a female ego. If a pronoun is used to address or refer to certain
male affines of a male ego the pronoun must be dual.
